<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,399,654,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Name derivation</emphasis>
: the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="2021" box="[524,678,655,680]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Neoceronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,678,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Neoceronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 
<emphasis box="[863,903,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">neo</emphasis>
(Greek, meaning new) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maskell" authorityYear="1895" box="[1218,1334,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceronema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1218,1334,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Ceronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(neuter), the genus it somewhat resembles.
</paragraph>
